{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850333130,"sessionID":"ses_287134055ffecuXkUAiE6OpdKT","part":{"id":"prt_d78ecf9f3001BYAO8SMSmZg5sj","messageID":"msg_d78ecd10f001ci8h3XvaWszuwv","sessionID":"ses_287134055ffecuXkUAiE6OpdKT","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_16721af3bc85472aa963c3cb","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-012: õ╝ÜĶ»ØÕŁśÕé©µÄźÕÅŻÕ«Üõ╣ē ŌĆö Delta Spec\n\n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThis AR defines the session storage interface for agentcube, providing a `Store` abstraction over Redis and Valkey backends for persisting sandbox metadata keyed by session id.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Scenario: Store interface provides session operations\n\n- **GIVEN** a configured Redis or Valkey backend\n- **WHEN** the `Store` interface is used\n- **THEN** the following methods are available:\n  - `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` ŌĆö verifies connectivity\n  - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` ŌĆö retrieves sandbox by session id\n  - `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error` ŌĆö creates new sandbox record\n  - `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error` ŌĆö updates existing sandbox\n  - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error` ŌĆö removes sandbox\n  - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` ŌĆö lists expired sessions\n  - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` ŌĆö lists inactive sessions\n  - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` ŌĆö updates last activity timestamp\n  - `Close() error` ŌĆö closes the store connection\n\n### Scenario: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE\n\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` is called for initialization\n- **THEN** the implementation is selected based on the value:\n  - `\"redis\"` (case-insensitive) ŌåÆ Redis implementation\n  - `\"valkey\"` (case-insensitive) ŌåÆ Valkey implementation\n  - Any other value ŌåÆ initialization fails\n\n### Scenario: Default provider is Redis\n\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n- **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed using default values\n\n### Scenario: Redis requires REDIS_ADDR\n\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is `redis` or unset\n- **WHEN** Redis store initializes without `REDIS_ADDR`\n- **THEN** initialization fails with error stating address required\n\n### Scenario: Redis password policy\n\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set\n- **WHEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not `\"false\"`\n- **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n- **AND** when `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`, empty password is allowed\n\n### Scenario: Valkey requires VALKEY_ADDR\n\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is `valkey`\n- **WHEN** Valkey store initializes without `VALKEY_ADDR`\n- **THEN** initialization fails with error stating address required\n\n### Scenario: Valkey password policy\n\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set\n- **WHEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty and `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not `\"false\"`\n- **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n- **AND** when `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`, empty password is allowed\n\n### Scenario: Valkey optional client options\n\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` is set to `\"true\"`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n- **THEN** `DisableCache` is set to `true` on `ClientOption`\n\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` is set to `\"true\"`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n- **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` is set to `true` on `ClientOption`\n\n### Scenario: Session key construction\n\n- **GIVEN** a session id `abc`\n- **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data\n- **THEN** the string key is `session:abc` (prefix `session:` concatenated with session id)\n\n### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation issues PING and expects string response `PONG`\n\n### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs\n- **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` (message: `\"store: not found\"`)\n\n### Scenario: StoreSandbox requires valid sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** nil sandbox passed to `StoreSandbox`\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n\n- **GIVEN** sandbox with zero `ExpiresAt` passed to `StoreSandbox`\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** error indicates invalid expiry\n\n### Scenario: StoreSandbox atomicity\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with `SessionID` and `ExpiresAt`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** the operation executes atomically:\n  - `SETNX` session key with JSON value\n  - `ZADD` session:expiry with score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n  - `ZADD` session:last_activity with score = `time.Now().Unix()`\n\n### Scenario: UpdateSandbox only updates value\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing session with key `session:{id}`\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs\n- **THEN** only the session JSON value is updated using SET with XX (key must exist)\n- **AND** expiry and last-activity ZSET entries are NOT modified\n\n### Scenario: UpdateSandbox on missing key fails\n\n- **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating key does not exist\n\n### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes all data\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing session\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` is called\n- **THEN** the operation removes:\n  - Session key (`session:{id}`)\n  - Member from `session:expiry` sorted set\n  - Member from `session:last_activity` sorted set\n\n### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes uses expiry index\n\n- **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n- **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n- **THEN** it selects members from `session:expiry` with scores from negative infinity through `before.Unix()`\n- **AND** returns up to `limit` entries\n- **AND** each entry's JSON is loaded and unmarshaled to `SandboxInfo`\n\n### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes uses activity index\n\n- **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n- **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n- **THEN** it selects members from `session:last_activity` with scores Ōēż `before.Unix()`\n- **AND** returns up to `limit` entries\n\n### Scenario: List with limit <= 0 returns nil\n\n- **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` or `ListInactiveSandboxes` called with limit <= 0\n- **WHEN** executed\n- **THEN** returns `nil, nil`\n\n### Scenario: List loaders tolerate missing keys\n\n- **GIVEN** a session id returned from ZSET but without corresponding string value\n- **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs\n- **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice\n- **AND** the operation does not fail for the whole batch\n\n### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity requires existing session\n\n- **GIVEN** empty session id\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned\n\n- **GIVEN** session id with no corresponding key\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n- **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound`\n\n### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity uses provided or current time\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing session\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with zero time\n- **THEN** `time.Now()` is used as the activity timestamp\n- **AND** ZADD updates `session:last_activity` with that score\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing session\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with non-zero time\n- **THEN** the provided timestamp is used as the activity score\n\n### Scenario: Singleton pattern ensures single initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()` concurrently\n- **WHEN** they run concurrently\n- **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once\n- **AND** subsequent calls return the same store instance\n- **AND** if initialization fails, `klog.Fatalf` is called\n\n### Scenario: Redis and Valkey implementations are functionally equivalent\n\n- **GIVEN** same input and configuration (adjusted for backend differences)\n- **WHEN** equivalent operations are performed\n- **THEN** both backends produce identical results for:\n  - Session CRUD operations\n  - Listing expired/inactive sessions\n  - Last activity updates\n  - Error semantics (`ErrNotFound`)\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n- `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n- `k8s.io/klog/v2`\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/store/store.go` | Store interface and errors |\n| `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Singleton pattern with `Storage()` |\n| `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Redis implementation |\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Valkey implementation |","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775850333120,"end":1775850333127}}}}
