{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850343621,"sessionID":"ses_287134055ffecuXkUAiE6OpdKT","part":{"id":"prt_d78edc884001kr1gvYHk5jDh7y","messageID":"msg_d78edb81e001ZpDI0MeVqdfLNo","sessionID":"ses_287134055ffecuXkUAiE6OpdKT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_647fc51bb5a2468284be6f3e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # delta-spec.md - K8s Reconciler Controller (AR-007)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: Module: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n6: Language: Go\n7: Size: L\n8: \n9: This specification defines the acceptance scenarios for the K8s Reconciler Controller, which provides an HTTP API server for managing `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n10: \n11: ---\n12: \n13: ## Requirement: AgentRuntime CRUD Operations\n14: \n15: ### Scenario: Create a new AgentRuntime\n16: \n17: **GIVEN** a valid `AgentRuntime` object with name, namespace, and spec  \n18: **WHEN** the client sends a POST request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes`  \n19: **THEN** the server creates the AgentRuntime in Kubernetes  \n20: **AND** returns HTTP 201 Created with the created AgentRuntime object\n21: \n22: ---\n23: \n24: ### Scenario: Get an existing AgentRuntime\n25: \n26: **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime in the cluster  \n27: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}`  \n28: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 200 OK with the AgentRuntime object\n29: \n30: ---\n31: \n32: ### Scenario: Get a non-existent AgentRuntime\n33: \n34: **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime with the specified name exists  \n35: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}`  \n36: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 404 NotFound with error details\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ### Scenario: List AgentRuntimes in a namespace\n41: \n42: **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntimes exist in a namespace  \n43: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes`  \n44: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 200 OK with a list of AgentRuntime objects  \n45: **AND** includes pagination metadata (Continue, RemainingItemCount, ResourceVersion)\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ### Scenario: Update an existing AgentRuntime\n50: \n51: **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime in the cluster  \n52: **WHEN** the client sends a PUT request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}`  \n53: **THEN** the server updates the AgentRuntime  \n54: **AND** returns HTTP 200 OK with the updated object\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ### Scenario: Delete an AgentRuntime\n59: \n60: **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime in the cluster  \n61: **WHEN** the client sends a DELETE request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}`  \n62: **THEN** the server deletes the AgentRuntime  \n63: **AND** returns HTTP 204 NoContent\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ### Scenario: Get AgentRuntime status\n68: \n69: **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime with status  \n70: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status`  \n71: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 200 OK with the status subresource\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ### Scenario: Patch AgentRuntime status\n76: \n77: **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime  \n78: **WHEN** the client sends a PATCH request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status` with valid patch data  \n79: **THEN** the server applies the patch to the status subresource  \n80: **AND** returns HTTP 200 OK with the patched object\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## Requirement: CodeInterpreter CRUD Operations\n85: \n86: ### Scenario: Create a new CodeInterpreter\n87: \n88: **GIVEN** a valid `CodeInterpreter` object with name, namespace, and spec  \n89: **WHEN** the client sends a POST request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters`  \n90: **THEN** the server creates the CodeInterpreter in Kubernetes  \n91: **AND** returns HTTP 201 Created with the created CodeInterpreter object\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ### Scenario: Get an existing CodeInterpreter\n96: \n97: **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter in the cluster  \n98: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}`  \n99: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 200 OK with the CodeInterpreter object\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ### Scenario: Get a non-existent CodeInterpreter\n104: \n105: **GIVEN** no CodeInterpreter with the specified name exists  \n106: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}`  \n107: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 404 NotFound with error details\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ### Scenario: List CodeInterpreters in a namespace\n112: \n113: **GIVEN** multiple CodeInterpreters exist in a namespace  \n114: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters`  \n115: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 200 OK with a list of CodeInterpreter objects  \n116: **AND** includes pagination metadata\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ### Scenario: Update an existing CodeInterpreter\n121: \n122: **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter in the cluster  \n123: **WHEN** the client sends a PUT request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}`  \n124: **THEN** the server updates the CodeInterpreter  \n125: **AND** returns HTTP 200 OK with the updated object\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ### Scenario: Delete a CodeInterpreter\n130: \n131: **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter in the cluster  \n132: **WHEN** the client sends a DELETE request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}`  \n133: **THEN** the server deletes the CodeInterpreter  \n134: **AND** returns HTTP 204 NoContent\n135: \n136: ---\n137: \n138: ### Scenario: Get CodeInterpreter status\n139: \n140: **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter with status  \n141: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status`  \n142: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 200 OK with the status subresource\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ### Scenario: Patch CodeInterpreter status\n147: \n148: **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter  \n149: **WHEN** the client sends a PATCH request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` with valid patch data  \n150: **THEN** the server applies the patch to the status subresource  \n151: **AND** returns HTTP 200 OK with the patched object\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## Requirement: Sandbox Operations\n156: \n157: ### Scenario: List sandboxes in a namespace\n158: \n159: **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes and CodeInterpreters with sessionId labels exist in a namespace  \n160: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes`  \n161: **THEN** the server returns a combined list of sandboxes from both resource types\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ### Scenario: Get sandbox by session ID\n166: \n167: **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with matching sessionId label  \n168: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{sessionId}`  \n169: **THEN** the server returns the matching sandbox\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ### Scenario: Get sandbox with non-existent session ID\n174: \n175: **GIVEN** no resource with the specified sessionId label exists  \n176: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{sessionId}`  \n177: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 404 NotFound with error \"sandbox not found\"\n178: \n179: ---\n180: \n181: ### Scenario: Delete sandbox by session ID\n182: \n183: **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with matching sessionId label  \n184: **WHEN** the client sends a DELETE request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{sessionId}`  \n185: **THEN** the server deletes the corresponding Kubernetes resource  \n186: **AND** returns HTTP 200 OK with DeleteResponse including deleted timestamp\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ### Scenario: Delete all sandboxes in namespace\n191: \n192: **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntimes and/or CodeInterpreters exist in a namespace  \n193: **WHEN** the client sends a DELETE request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes?deleteAll=true`  \n194: **THEN** the server deletes all matching sandboxes  \n195: **AND** returns HTTP 200 OK with BatchDeleteResponse (DeletedCount, FailedCount)\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: ### Scenario: Delete all sandboxes without deleteAll parameter\n200: \n201: **GIVEN** multiple sandboxes exist in a namespace  \n202: **WHEN** the client sends a DELETE request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` without deleteAll query parameter  \n203: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 400 BadRequest\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## Requirement: Server Lifecycle\n208: \n209: ### Scenario: Start HTTP server\n210: \n211: **GIVEN** a valid Server configuration with port and WorkloadManager  \n212: **WHEN** `Server.Start()` is called  \n213: **THEN** the server binds to the configured port  \n214: **AND** begins accepting HTTP connections  \n215: **AND** sets ready state to true\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ### Scenario: Stop HTTP server gracefully\n220: \n221: **GIVEN** a running HTTP server  \n222: **WHEN** `Server.Stop()` is called  \n223: **THEN** the server stops accepting new connections  \n224: **AND** waits for in-flight requests to complete within ShutdownTimeout  \n225: **AND** closes the WorkloadManager  \n226: **AND** sets ready state to false\n227: \n228: ---\n229: \n230: ### Scenario: Health check endpoint\n231: \n232: **GIVEN** a running server  \n233: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/healthz`  \n234: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 200 OK with \"ok\"\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ### Scenario: Readiness check when ready\n239: \n240: **GIVEN** a running server with ready state set to true  \n241: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/readyz`  \n242: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 200 OK with status \"ok\"\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ### Scenario: Readiness check when not ready\n247: \n248: **GIVEN** a server with ready state set to false  \n249: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/readyz`  \n250: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 503 ServiceUnavailable with status \"not ready\"\n251: \n252: ---\n253: \n254: ## Requirement: Error Handling\n255: \n256: ### Scenario: Bad request - invalid JSON\n257: \n258: **GIVEN** an invalid JSON payload in create request  \n259: **WHEN** the client sends a POST request  \n260: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 400 BadRequest with error details\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ### Scenario: Conflict - resource already exists\n265: \n266: **GIVEN** attempting to create a resource with same name as existing  \n267: **WHEN** the client sends a POST request  \n268: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 409 Conflict\n269: \n270: ---\n271: \n272: ### Scenario: Invalid resource\n273: \n274: **GIVEN** an invalid resource specification  \n275: **WHEN** the client sends a create or update request  \n276: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 422 UnprocessableEntity\n277: \n278: ---\n279: \n280: ### Scenario: Invalid query parameters\n281: \n282: **GIVEN** invalid query parameters in list request  \n283: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request  \n284: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 400 BadRequest\n285: \n286: ---\n287: \n288: ## Requirement: CORS Support\n289: \n290: ### Scenario: CORS preflight request\n291: \n292: **GIVEN** a browser client sending OPTIONS request  \n293: **WHEN** the client sends a request with Access-Control-Request-Method header  \n294: **THEN** the server responds with HTTP 204 NoContent  \n295: **AND** includes CORS headers (Access-Control-Allow-Origin, Access-Control-Allow-Methods, Access-Control-Allow-Headers)\n296: \n297: ---\n298: \n299: ## Requirement: WorkloadManager Interface\n300: \n301: ### Scenario: Create AgentRuntime through WorkloadManager\n302: \n303: **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager instance with valid client-go client  \n304: **WHEN** `CreateAgentRuntime` is called with context, namespace, object, and options  \n305: **THEN** it delegates to the client and returns the created object\n306: \n307: ---\n308: \n309: ### Scenario: Get AgentRuntime status through WorkloadManager\n310: \n311: **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime in the cluster  \n312: **WHEN** `GetAgentRuntimeStatus` is called  \n313: **THEN** it returns the Status subresource\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ### Scenario: Watch AgentRuntimes\n318: \n319: **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager instance  \n320: **WHEN** `WatchAgentRuntimes` is called with list options  \n321: **THEN** it returns a watch.Interface for watching changes\n322: \n323: ---\n324: \n325: ### Scenario: Close WorkloadManager\n326: \n327: **GIVEN** an open WorkloadManager  \n328: **WHEN** `Close()` is called  \n329: **THEN** it performs cleanup and returns nil\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ## Requirement: Label-based Operations\n334: \n335: ### Scenario: List sandboxes with label selector\n336: \n337: **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes and CodeInterpreters with various labels  \n338: **WHEN** the client sends a GET to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes?labelSelector=app=test`  \n339: **THEN** the server returns only resources matching the label selector\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ### Scenario: Delete sandbox with label selector\n344: \n345: **GIVEN** resources with specific labels  \n346: **WHEN** delete request includes label selector  \n347: **THEN** the server applies label selector when finding matching resources\n348: \n349: ---\n350: \n351: ## Requirement: Graceful Deletion\n352: \n353: ### Scenario: Force delete sandbox\n354: \n355: **GIVEN** a sandbox in terminating state  \n356: **WHEN** delete is called with force=true (gracePeriodSeconds=0)  \n357: **THEN** the server immediately deletes the resource without waiting for finalizers\n358: \n359: ---\n360: \n361: ### Scenario: Delete sandbox with grace period\n362: \n363: **GIVEN** a sandbox with finalizers  \n364: **WHEN** delete is called with gracePeriodSeconds > 0  \n365: **THEN** the server sets the deletion timestamp and waits for grace period\n\n(End of file - total 365 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# delta-spec.md - K8s Reconciler Controller (AR-007)\n\n## Overview\n\nModule: `pkg/workloadmanager`\nLanguage: Go\nSize: L\n\nThis specification defines the acceptance scenarios for the K8s Reconciler Controller, which provides an HTTP API server for managing `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: AgentRuntime CRUD Operations\n\n### Scenario: Create a new AgentRuntime\n\n**GIVEN** a valid `AgentRuntime` object with name, namespace, and spec  \n**WHEN** the client sends a POST request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes`  \n**THEN** the server creates the AgentRuntime in Kubernetes  \n**AND** returns HTTP 201 Created with the created AgentRuntime object","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775850343611,"end":1775850343619}}}}
