{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850411609,"sessionID":"ses_287134055ffecuXkUAiE6OpdKT","part":{"id":"prt_d78edf70f001e9RZk2lgWayU3N","messageID":"msg_d78ede33a001wjxR9NlgpZk7EV","sessionID":"ses_287134055ffecuXkUAiE6OpdKT","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_f1e5fe88fb4c40a5894c082f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","newString":"# Delta Spec: AR-012 ŌĆö õ╝ÜĶ»ØÕŁśÕé©µÄźÕÅŻÕ«Üõ╣ē\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session storage interface in `pkg/store`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-012\n- **Module**: `pkg/store`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n- **Base Specs**: \n  - `deployment/client-go.md` ŌĆö Kubernetes client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh API\n  - `session-store/design.md` ŌĆö Session store design with Store interface\n  - `session-store/spec.md` ŌĆö Session store specification with requirements\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe agentcube system requires a session storage abstraction to persist sandbox metadata keyed by session id. The store module provides a unified interface over Redis and Valkey backends, with support for:\n- Session CRUD operations (create, read, update, delete)\n- Expiry-based and activity-based session listing for garbage collection\n- Index maintenance via sorted sets\n- Provider selection via environment variables\n- Singleton initialization pattern\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Store Interface Contract\n\n### Scenario: Store interface provides all required methods\n\n**GIVEN** a configured Redis or Valkey backend  \n**WHEN** the `Store` interface is used  \n**THEN** the following methods are available:\n- `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` ŌĆö verifies connectivity\n- `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` ŌĆö retrieves sandbox by session id\n- `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error` ŌĆö creates new sandbox record\n- `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error` ŌĆö updates existing sandbox\n- `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error` ŌĆö removes sandbox\n- `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` ŌĆö lists expired sessions\n- `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` ŌĆö lists inactive sessions\n- `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` ŌĆö updates last activity timestamp\n- `Close() error` ŌĆö closes the store connection\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Provider Selection\n\n### Scenario: STORE_TYPE selects Redis provider\n\n**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"redis\"` (case-insensitive)  \n**WHEN** `Storage()` is called for initialization  \n**THEN** Redis implementation is constructed using environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD`\n\n### Scenario: STORE_TYPE selects Valkey provider\n\n**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"valkey\"` (case-insensitive)  \n**WHEN** `Storage()` is called for initialization  \n**THEN** Valkey implementation is constructed using environment variables `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n\n### Scenario: Default provider is Redis when STORE_TYPE unset\n\n**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set  \n**WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes  \n**THEN** Redis implementation is constructed by default\n\n### Scenario: Invalid STORE_TYPE fails initialization\n\n**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to an unsupported value (e.g., `\"memcached\"`)  \n**WHEN** `Storage()` is called  \n**THEN** initialization fails with error indicating unsupported store type\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Redis Environment Configuration\n\n### Scenario: Redis requires REDIS_ADDR\n\n**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is `redis` or unset  \n**WHEN** Redis store initializes without `REDIS_ADDR` environment variable  \n**THEN** initialization fails with error stating REDIS_ADDR is required\n\n### Scenario: Redis password required by default\n\n**GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not `\"false\"`  \n**WHEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty or not set  \n**THEN** initialization fails with error stating password is required\n\n### Scenario: Redis password optional when explicitly disabled\n\n**GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set  \n**AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`  \n**WHEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty  \n**THEN** initialization succeeds without password\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Valkey Environment Configuration\n\n### Scenario: Valkey requires VALKEY_ADDR\n\n**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is `valkey`  \n**WHEN** Valkey store initializes without `VALKEY_ADDR` environment variable  \n**THEN** initialization fails with error stating VALKEY_ADDR is required\n\n### Scenario: Valkey password required by default\n\n**GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set and `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not `\"false\"`  \n**WHEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty or not set  \n**THEN** initialization fails with error stating password is required\n\n### Scenario: Valkey password optional when explicitly disabled\n\n**GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set  \n**AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`  \n**WHEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty  \n**THEN** initialization succeeds without password\n\n### Scenario: Valkey DisableCache option from environment\n\n**GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` is set to `\"true\"`  \n**WHEN** Valkey client options are built  \n**THEN** `DisableCache` is set to `true` on `ClientOption`\n\n### Scenario: Valkey ForceSingleClient option from environment\n\n**GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` is set to `\"true\"`  \n**WHEN** Valkey client options are built  \n**THEN** `ForceSingleClient` is set to `true` on `ClientOption`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Key Naming\n\n### Scenario: Session key uses prefix concatenation\n\n**GIVEN** a session id `abc-123`  \n**WHEN** the store writes sandbox data  \n**THEN** the string key is `session:abc-123` (prefix `\"session:\"` concatenated with session id)\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Ping Connectivity Verification\n\n### Scenario: Redis ping returns PONG\n\n**GIVEN** a healthy Redis server  \n**WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called on Redis store  \n**THEN** the implementation issues PING command  \n**AND** expects string response `\"PONG\"`\n\n### Scenario: Valkey ping returns PONG\n\n**GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server  \n**WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called on Valkey store  \n**THEN** the implementation issues `B().Ping()`  \n**AND** expects string response `\"PONG\"`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Not Found Semantics\n\n### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n\n**GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend  \n**WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs with non-existent session id  \n**THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` with message `\"store: not found\"`\n\n### Scenario: Redis backend returns Nil for missing key\n\n**GIVEN** Redis store  \n**WHEN** GET command returns Redis `Nil`  \n**THEN** `ErrNotFound` is returned\n\n### Scenario: Valkey backend returns nil for missing key\n\n**GIVEN** Valkey store  \n**WHEN** GET command returns `IsValkeyNil` true  \n**THEN** `ErrNotFound` is returned\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: StoreSandbox Validation\n\n### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n\n**GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called  \n**WHEN** the method executes  \n**THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n\n### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n\n**GIVEN** `StoreSandbox` is called with sandbox where `ExpiresAt` is zero time  \n**WHEN** the method validates input  \n**THEN** error indicates invalid expiry\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: StoreSandbox Atomicity\n\n### Scenario: StoreSandbox creates session with all indexes\n\n**GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with `SessionID`, `ExpiresAt`, and other fields  \n**WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called  \n**THEN** the operation executes atomically:\n- Session key (`session:{id}`) is set with JSON value using SETNX\n- `session:expiry` ZSET gets member with score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n- `session:last_activity` ZSET gets member with score = `time.Now().Unix()`\n\n### Scenario: StoreSandbox fails on any pipeline error\n\n**GIVEN** Redis/Valkey pipeline/multi operation  \n**WHEN** any command in the batch fails  \n**THEN** the operation returns error and no partial state is left\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: UpdateSandbox Semantics\n\n### Scenario: UpdateSandbox only modifies session value\n\n**GIVEN** an existing session with key `session:{id}`  \n**WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called with new sandbox data  \n**THEN** only the session JSON value is updated using SET with XX flag  \n**AND** expiry and last-activity ZSET entries are NOT modified\n\n### Scenario: UpdateSandbox fails on missing key\n\n**GIVEN** no session key exists for the given session id  \n**WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called  \n**THEN** error is returned indicating key does not exist (Redis: SETXX returns false; Valkey: response not \"OK\")\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID Cleanup\n\n### Scenario: Delete removes session key and both indexes\n\n**GIVEN** an existing session with data in all three keys  \n**WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` is called  \n**THEN** the operation removes:\n- Session key (`session:{id}`) via DEL\n- Member from `session:expiry` ZSET via ZREM\n- Member from `session:last_activity` ZSET via ZREM\n\n### Scenario: Delete executes atomically\n\n**GIVEN** a valid session id  \n**WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` runs  \n**THEN** all delete operations execute in one pipeline/multi block\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: ListExpiredSandboxes Operation\n\n### Scenario: ListExpired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on expiry index\n\n**GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0  \n**WHEN** the implementation queries the index  \n**THEN** it selects members from `session:expiry` with scores from negative infinity to `before.Unix()`  \n**AND** limited to `limit` entries\n\n### Scenario: ListExpired with limit <= 0 returns nil\n\n**GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` called with limit <= 0  \n**WHEN** executed  \n**THEN** returns `nil, nil`\n\n### Scenario: ListExpired loads JSON for each session id\n\n**GIVEN** ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session ids  \n**WHEN** fetching sandbox data  \n**THEN** each id is used to GET the corresponding `session:{id}` key  \n**AND** JSON is unmarshaled to `SandboxInfo`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: ListInactiveSandboxes Operation\n\n### Scenario: ListInactive uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity index\n\n**GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0  \n**WHEN** the implementation queries the index  \n**THEN** it selects members from `session:last_activity` with scores Ōēż `before.Unix()`  \n**AND** limited to `limit` entries\n\n### Scenario: ListInactive with limit <= 0 returns nil\n\n**GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes` called with limit <= 0  \n**WHEN** executed  \n**THEN** returns `nil, nil`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: List Operations Tolerate Missing Keys\n\n### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member is skipped\n\n**GIVEN** a session id returned from ZSET but without corresponding string value  \n**WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs  \n**THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice  \n**AND** the operation does not fail for the whole batch\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n\n### Scenario: Empty session id rejected\n\n**GIVEN** empty session id  \n**WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called  \n**THEN** error is returned\n\n### Scenario: Zero time uses current time\n\n**GIVEN** an existing session  \n**WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with zero time  \n**THEN** `time.Now()` is used as the activity timestamp\n\n### Scenario: Non-zero time uses provided value\n\n**GIVEN** an existing session  \n**WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with non-zero `at` timestamp  \n**THEN** the provided timestamp is used as the activity score in ZADD\n\n### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity requires existing session\n\n**GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key exists  \n**WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called  \n**THEN** error is `ErrNotFound`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Singleton Initialization\n\n### Scenario: Storage returns singleton instance\n\n**GIVEN** `Storage()` is called multiple times  \n**WHEN** after first initialization  \n**THEN** the same store instance is returned every time\n\n### Scenario: Concurrent Storage calls initialize once\n\n**GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()` concurrently  \n**WHEN** they execute concurrently  \n**THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once via `sync.Once`\n\n### Scenario: Init failure triggers fatal log\n\n**GIVEN** store initialization fails  \n**WHEN** `Storage()` is called  \n**THEN** `klog.Fatalf` is called with error message\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Redis and Valkey Equivalence\n\n### Scenario: Both backends implement same interface\n\n**GIVEN** Redis and Valkey stores with equivalent configuration  \n**WHEN** equivalent operations are performed  \n**THEN** both backends produce identical results for:\n- Session CRUD operations\n- Listing expired/inactive sessions\n- Last activity updates\n- Error semantics (`ErrNotFound`)\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Store interface defined in `pkg/store/store.go`\n- [ ] ErrNotFound error defined and returned for missing sessions\n- [ ] Redis implementation in `pkg/store/store_redis.go`\n- [ ] Valkey implementation in `pkg/store/store_valkey.go`\n- [ ] Singleton pattern in `pkg/store/singleton.go` with `Storage()` function\n- [ ] Environment variables parsed correctly for both providers\n- [ ] Password policy enforced (required by default, optional when disabled)\n- [ ] Session key naming uses `session:` prefix\n- [ ] Expiry index maintained via `session:expiry` ZSET\n- [ ] Last activity index maintained via `session:last_activity` ZSET\n- [ ] Atomic operations for Store, Update, Delete\n- [ ] List operations with limit <= 0 return nil\n- [ ] Orphan ZSET members handled gracefully\n- [ ] All acceptance scenarios pass verification\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md`\n- Base Spec: `deployment/client-go.md`\n- Base Spec: `session-store/design.md`\n- Base Spec: `session-store/spec.md`","oldString":"# Delta Spec: AR-012 ŌĆö õ╝ÜĶ»ØÕŁśÕé©µÄźÕÅŻÕ«Üõ╣ē\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session storage interface in `pkg/store`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-012\n- **Module**: `pkg/store`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\n\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Storage Interface\n\n### Scenario: \n\n**GIVEN** \n**WHEN** \n**THEN** \n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] \n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md`"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md\n@@ -9,32 +9,389 @@\n - **AR**: AR-012\n - **Module**: `pkg/store`\n - **Language**: Go\n - **Size**: S\n+- **Base Specs**: \n+  - `deployment/client-go.md` ŌĆö Kubernetes client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh API\n+  - `session-store/design.md` ŌĆö Session store design with Store interface\n+  - `session-store/spec.md` ŌĆö Session store specification with requirements\n \n ---\n \n ## Background\n \n+The agentcube system requires a session storage abstraction to persist sandbox metadata keyed by session id. The store module provides a unified interface over Redis and Valkey backends, with support for:\n+- Session CRUD operations (create, read, update, delete)\n+- Expiry-based and activity-based session listing for garbage collection\n+- Index maintenance via sorted sets\n+- Provider selection via environment variables\n+- Singleton initialization pattern\n \n+---\n \n+## Requirement: Store Interface Contract\n+\n+### Scenario: Store interface provides all required methods\n+\n+**GIVEN** a configured Redis or Valkey backend  \n+**WHEN** the `Store` interface is used  \n+**THEN** the following methods are available:\n+- `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` ŌĆö verifies connectivity\n+- `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` ŌĆö retrieves sandbox by session id\n+- `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error` ŌĆö creates new sandbox record\n+- `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error` ŌĆö updates existing sandbox\n+- `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error` ŌĆö removes sandbox\n+- `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` ŌĆö lists expired sessions\n+- `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` ŌĆö lists inactive sessions\n+- `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` ŌĆö updates last activity timestamp\n+- `Close() error` ŌĆö closes the store connection\n+\n ---\n \n-## Requirement: Session Storage Interface\n+## Requirement: Provider Selection\n \n-### Scenario: \n+### Scenario: STORE_TYPE selects Redis provider\n \n-**GIVEN** \n-**WHEN** \n-**THEN** \n+**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"redis\"` (case-insensitive)  \n+**WHEN** `Storage()` is called for initialization  \n+**THEN** Redis implementation is constructed using environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD`\n \n+### Scenario: STORE_TYPE selects Valkey provider\n+\n+**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"valkey\"` (case-insensitive)  \n+**WHEN** `Storage()` is called for initialization  \n+**THEN** Valkey implementation is constructed using environment variables `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n+\n+### Scenario: Default provider is Redis when STORE_TYPE unset\n+\n+**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set  \n+**WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes  \n+**THEN** Redis implementation is constructed by default\n+\n+### Scenario: Invalid STORE_TYPE fails initialization\n+\n+**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to an unsupported value (e.g., `\"memcached\"`)  \n+**WHEN** `Storage()` is called  \n+**THEN** initialization fails with error indicating unsupported store type\n+\n ---\n \n+## Requirement: Redis Environment Configuration\n+\n+### Scenario: Redis requires REDIS_ADDR\n+\n+**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is `redis` or unset  \n+**WHEN** Redis store initializes without `REDIS_ADDR` environment variable  \n+**THEN** initialization fails with error stating REDIS_ADDR is required\n+\n+### Scenario: Redis password required by default\n+\n+**GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not `\"false\"`  \n+**WHEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty or not set  \n+**THEN** initialization fails with error stating password is required\n+\n+### Scenario: Redis password optional when explicitly disabled\n+\n+**GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set  \n+**AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`  \n+**WHEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty  \n+**THEN** initialization succeeds without password\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Valkey Environment Configuration\n+\n+### Scenario: Valkey requires VALKEY_ADDR\n+\n+**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is `valkey`  \n+**WHEN** Valkey store initializes without `VALKEY_ADDR` environment variable  \n+**THEN** initialization fails with error stating VALKEY_ADDR is required\n+\n+### Scenario: Valkey password required by default\n+\n+**GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set and `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not `\"false\"`  \n+**WHEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty or not set  \n+**THEN** initialization fails with error stating password is required\n+\n+### Scenario: Valkey password optional when explicitly disabled\n+\n+**GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set  \n+**AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`  \n+**WHEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty  \n+**THEN** initialization succeeds without password\n+\n+### Scenario: Valkey DisableCache option from environment\n+\n+**GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` is set to `\"true\"`  \n+**WHEN** Valkey client options are built  \n+**THEN** `DisableCache` is set to `true` on `ClientOption`\n+\n+### Scenario: Valkey ForceSingleClient option from environment\n+\n+**GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` is set to `\"true\"`  \n+**WHEN** Valkey client options are built  \n+**THEN** `ForceSingleClient` is set to `true` on `ClientOption`\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Session Key Naming\n+\n+### Scenario: Session key uses prefix concatenation\n+\n+**GIVEN** a session id `abc-123`  \n+**WHEN** the store writes sandbox data  \n+**THEN** the string key is `session:abc-123` (prefix `\"session:\"` concatenated with session id)\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Ping Connectivity Verification\n+\n+### Scenario: Redis ping returns PONG\n+\n+**GIVEN** a healthy Redis server  \n+**WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called on Redis store  \n+**THEN** the implementation issues PING command  \n+**AND** expects string response `\"PONG\"`\n+\n+### Scenario: Valkey ping returns PONG\n+\n+**GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server  \n+**WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called on Valkey store  \n+**THEN** the implementation issues `B().Ping()`  \n+**AND** expects string response `\"PONG\"`\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Not Found Semantics\n+\n+### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n+\n+**GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend  \n+**WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs with non-existent session id  \n+**THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` with message `\"store: not found\"`\n+\n+### Scenario: Redis backend returns Nil for missing key\n+\n+**GIVEN** Redis store  \n+**WHEN** GET command returns Redis `Nil`  \n+**THEN** `ErrNotFound` is returned\n+\n+### Scenario: Valkey backend returns nil for missing key\n+\n+**GIVEN** Valkey store  \n+**WHEN** GET command returns `IsValkeyNil` true  \n+**THEN** `ErrNotFound` is returned\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: StoreSandbox Validation\n+\n+### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n+\n+**GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called  \n+**WHEN** the method executes  \n+**THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n+\n+### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n+\n+**GIVEN** `StoreSandbox` is called with sandbox where `ExpiresAt` is zero time  \n+**WHEN** the method validates input  \n+**THEN** error indicates invalid expiry\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: StoreSandbox Atomicity\n+\n+### Scenario: StoreSandbox creates session with all indexes\n+\n+**GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with `SessionID`, `ExpiresAt`, and other fields  \n+**WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called  \n+**THEN** the operation executes atomically:\n+- Session key (`session:{id}`) is set with JSON value using SETNX\n+- `session:expiry` ZSET gets member with score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n+- `session:last_activity` ZSET gets member with score = `time.Now().Unix()`\n+\n+### Scenario: StoreSandbox fails on any pipeline error\n+\n+**GIVEN** Redis/Valkey pipeline/multi operation  \n+**WHEN** any command in the batch fails  \n+**THEN** the operation returns error and no partial state is left\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: UpdateSandbox Semantics\n+\n+### Scenario: UpdateSandbox only modifies session value\n+\n+**GIVEN** an existing session with key `session:{id}`  \n+**WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called with new sandbox data  \n+**THEN** only the session JSON value is updated using SET with XX flag  \n+**AND** expiry and last-activity ZSET entries are NOT modified\n+\n+### Scenario: UpdateSandbox fails on missing key\n+\n+**GIVEN** no session key exists for the given session id  \n+**WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called  \n+**THEN** error is returned indicating key does not exist (Redis: SETXX returns false; Valkey: response not \"OK\")\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID Cleanup\n+\n+### Scenario: Delete removes session key and both indexes\n+\n+**GIVEN** an existing session with data in all three keys  \n+**WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` is called  \n+**THEN** the operation removes:\n+- Session key (`session:{id}`) via DEL\n+- Member from `session:expiry` ZSET via ZREM\n+- Member from `session:last_activity` ZSET via ZREM\n+\n+### Scenario: Delete executes atomically\n+\n+**GIVEN** a valid session id  \n+**WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` runs  \n+**THEN** all delete operations execute in one pipeline/multi block\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: ListExpiredSandboxes Operation\n+\n+### Scenario: ListExpired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on expiry index\n+\n+**GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0  \n+**WHEN** the implementation queries the index  \n+**THEN** it selects members from `session:expiry` with scores from negative infinity to `before.Unix()`  \n+**AND** limited to `limit` entries\n+\n+### Scenario: ListExpired with limit <= 0 returns nil\n+\n+**GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` called with limit <= 0  \n+**WHEN** executed  \n+**THEN** returns `nil, nil`\n+\n+### Scenario: ListExpired loads JSON for each session id\n+\n+**GIVEN** ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session ids  \n+**WHEN** fetching sandbox data  \n+**THEN** each id is used to GET the corresponding `session:{id}` key  \n+**AND** JSON is unmarshaled to `SandboxInfo`\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: ListInactiveSandboxes Operation\n+\n+### Scenario: ListInactive uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity index\n+\n+**GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0  \n+**WHEN** the implementation queries the index  \n+**THEN** it selects members from `session:last_activity` with scores Ōēż `before.Unix()`  \n+**AND** limited to `limit` entries\n+\n+### Scenario: ListInactive with limit <= 0 returns nil\n+\n+**GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes` called with limit <= 0  \n+**WHEN** executed  \n+**THEN** returns `nil, nil`\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: List Operations Tolerate Missing Keys\n+\n+### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member is skipped\n+\n+**GIVEN** a session id returned from ZSET but without corresponding string value  \n+**WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs  \n+**THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice  \n+**AND** the operation does not fail for the whole batch\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n+\n+### Scenario: Empty session id rejected\n+\n+**GIVEN** empty session id  \n+**WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called  \n+**THEN** error is returned\n+\n+### Scenario: Zero time uses current time\n+\n+**GIVEN** an existing session  \n+**WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with zero time  \n+**THEN** `time.Now()` is used as the activity timestamp\n+\n+### Scenario: Non-zero time uses provided value\n+\n+**GIVEN** an existing session  \n+**WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with non-zero `at` timestamp  \n+**THEN** the provided timestamp is used as the activity score in ZADD\n+\n+### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity requires existing session\n+\n+**GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key exists  \n+**WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called  \n+**THEN** error is `ErrNotFound`\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Singleton Initialization\n+\n+### Scenario: Storage returns singleton instance\n+\n+**GIVEN** `Storage()` is called multiple times  \n+**WHEN** after first initialization  \n+**THEN** the same store instance is returned every time\n+\n+### Scenario: Concurrent Storage calls initialize once\n+\n+**GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()` concurrently  \n+**WHEN** they execute concurrently  \n+**THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once via `sync.Once`\n+\n+### Scenario: Init failure triggers fatal log\n+\n+**GIVEN** store initialization fails  \n+**WHEN** `Storage()` is called  \n+**THEN** `klog.Fatalf` is called with error message\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Redis and Valkey Equivalence\n+\n+### Scenario: Both backends implement same interface\n+\n+**GIVEN** Redis and Valkey stores with equivalent configuration  \n+**WHEN** equivalent operations are performed  \n+**THEN** both backends produce identical results for:\n+- Session CRUD operations\n+- Listing expired/inactive sessions\n+- Last activity updates\n+- Error semantics (`ErrNotFound`)\n+\n+---\n+\n ## Acceptance Criteria\n \n-- [ ] \n+- [ ] Store interface defined in `pkg/store/store.go`\n+- [ ] ErrNotFound error defined and returned for missing sessions\n+- [ ] Redis implementation in `pkg/store/store_redis.go`\n+- [ ] Valkey implementation in `pkg/store/store_valkey.go`\n+- [ ] Singleton pattern in `pkg/store/singleton.go` with `Storage()` function\n+- [ ] Environment variables parsed correctly for both providers\n+- [ ] Password policy enforced (required by default, optional when disabled)\n+- [ ] Session key naming uses `session:` prefix\n+- [ ] Expiry index maintained via `session:expiry` ZSET\n+- [ ] Last activity index maintained via `session:last_activity` ZSET\n+- [ ] Atomic operations for Store, Update, Delete\n+- [ ] List operations with limit <= 0 return nil\n+- [ ] Orphan ZSET members handled gracefully\n+- [ ] All acceptance scenarios pass verification\n \n ---\n \n ## References\n \n-- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md`\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md`\n+- Base Spec: `deployment/client-go.md`\n+- Base Spec: `session-store/design.md`\n+- Base Spec: `session-store/spec.md`\n\\ No newline at end of file\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","before":"# Delta Spec: AR-012 ŌĆö õ╝ÜĶ»ØÕŁśÕé©µÄźÕÅŻÕ«Üõ╣ē\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session storage interface in `pkg/store`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-012\n- **Module**: `pkg/store`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\n\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Storage Interface\n\n### Scenario: \n\n**GIVEN** \n**WHEN** \n**THEN** \n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] \n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md`","after":"# Delta Spec: AR-012 ŌĆö õ╝ÜĶ»ØÕŁśÕé©µÄźÕÅŻÕ«Üõ╣ē\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session storage interface in `pkg/store`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-012\n- **Module**: `pkg/store`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n- **Base Specs**: \n  - `deployment/client-go.md` ŌĆö Kubernetes client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh API\n  - `session-store/design.md` ŌĆö Session store design with Store interface\n  - `session-store/spec.md` ŌĆö Session store specification with requirements\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe agentcube system requires a session storage abstraction to persist sandbox metadata keyed by session id. The store module provides a unified interface over Redis and Valkey backends, with support for:\n- Session CRUD operations (create, read, update, delete)\n- Expiry-based and activity-based session listing for garbage collection\n- Index maintenance via sorted sets\n- Provider selection via environment variables\n- Singleton initialization pattern\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Store Interface Contract\n\n### Scenario: Store interface provides all required methods\n\n**GIVEN** a configured Redis or Valkey backend  \n**WHEN** the `Store` interface is used  \n**THEN** the following methods are available:\n- `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` ŌĆö verifies connectivity\n- `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` ŌĆö retrieves sandbox by session id\n- `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error` ŌĆö creates new sandbox record\n- `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error` ŌĆö updates existing sandbox\n- `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error` ŌĆö removes sandbox\n- `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` ŌĆö lists expired sessions\n- `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` ŌĆö lists inactive sessions\n- `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` ŌĆö updates last activity timestamp\n- `Close() error` ŌĆö closes the store connection\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Provider Selection\n\n### Scenario: STORE_TYPE selects Redis provider\n\n**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"redis\"` (case-insensitive)  \n**WHEN** `Storage()` is called for initialization  \n**THEN** Redis implementation is constructed using environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD`\n\n### Scenario: STORE_TYPE selects Valkey provider\n\n**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"valkey\"` (case-insensitive)  \n**WHEN** `Storage()` is called for initialization  \n**THEN** Valkey implementation is constructed using environment variables `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n\n### Scenario: Default provider is Redis when STORE_TYPE unset\n\n**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set  \n**WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes  \n**THEN** Redis implementation is constructed by default\n\n### Scenario: Invalid STORE_TYPE fails initialization\n\n**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to an unsupported value (e.g., `\"memcached\"`)  \n**WHEN** `Storage()` is called  \n**THEN** initialization fails with error indicating unsupported store type\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Redis Environment Configuration\n\n### Scenario: Redis requires REDIS_ADDR\n\n**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is `redis` or unset  \n**WHEN** Redis store initializes without `REDIS_ADDR` environment variable  \n**THEN** initialization fails with error stating REDIS_ADDR is required\n\n### Scenario: Redis password required by default\n\n**GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not `\"false\"`  \n**WHEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty or not set  \n**THEN** initialization fails with error stating password is required\n\n### Scenario: Redis password optional when explicitly disabled\n\n**GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set  \n**AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`  \n**WHEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty  \n**THEN** initialization succeeds without password\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Valkey Environment Configuration\n\n### Scenario: Valkey requires VALKEY_ADDR\n\n**GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is `valkey`  \n**WHEN** Valkey store initializes without `VALKEY_ADDR` environment variable  \n**THEN** initialization fails with error stating VALKEY_ADDR is required\n\n### Scenario: Valkey password required by default\n\n**GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set and `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not `\"false\"`  \n**WHEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty or not set  \n**THEN** initialization fails with error stating password is required\n\n### Scenario: Valkey password optional when explicitly disabled\n\n**GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set  \n**AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`  \n**WHEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty  \n**THEN** initialization succeeds without password\n\n### Scenario: Valkey DisableCache option from environment\n\n**GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` is set to `\"true\"`  \n**WHEN** Valkey client options are built  \n**THEN** `DisableCache` is set to `true` on `ClientOption`\n\n### Scenario: Valkey ForceSingleClient option from environment\n\n**GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` is set to `\"true\"`  \n**WHEN** Valkey client options are built  \n**THEN** `ForceSingleClient` is set to `true` on `ClientOption`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Key Naming\n\n### Scenario: Session key uses prefix concatenation\n\n**GIVEN** a session id `abc-123`  \n**WHEN** the store writes sandbox data  \n**THEN** the string key is `session:abc-123` (prefix `\"session:\"` concatenated with session id)\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Ping Connectivity Verification\n\n### Scenario: Redis ping returns PONG\n\n**GIVEN** a healthy Redis server  \n**WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called on Redis store  \n**THEN** the implementation issues PING command  \n**AND** expects string response `\"PONG\"`\n\n### Scenario: Valkey ping returns PONG\n\n**GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server  \n**WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called on Valkey store  \n**THEN** the implementation issues `B().Ping()`  \n**AND** expects string response `\"PONG\"`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Not Found Semantics\n\n### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n\n**GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend  \n**WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs with non-existent session id  \n**THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` with message `\"store: not found\"`\n\n### Scenario: Redis backend returns Nil for missing key\n\n**GIVEN** Redis store  \n**WHEN** GET command returns Redis `Nil`  \n**THEN** `ErrNotFound` is returned\n\n### Scenario: Valkey backend returns nil for missing key\n\n**GIVEN** Valkey store  \n**WHEN** GET command returns `IsValkeyNil` true  \n**THEN** `ErrNotFound` is returned\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: StoreSandbox Validation\n\n### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n\n**GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called  \n**WHEN** the method executes  \n**THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n\n### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n\n**GIVEN** `StoreSandbox` is called with sandbox where `ExpiresAt` is zero time  \n**WHEN** the method validates input  \n**THEN** error indicates invalid expiry\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: StoreSandbox Atomicity\n\n### Scenario: StoreSandbox creates session with all indexes\n\n**GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with `SessionID`, `ExpiresAt`, and other fields  \n**WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called  \n**THEN** the operation executes atomically:\n- Session key (`session:{id}`) is set with JSON value using SETNX\n- `session:expiry` ZSET gets member with score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n- `session:last_activity` ZSET gets member with score = `time.Now().Unix()`\n\n### Scenario: StoreSandbox fails on any pipeline error\n\n**GIVEN** Redis/Valkey pipeline/multi operation  \n**WHEN** any command in the batch fails  \n**THEN** the operation returns error and no partial state is left\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: UpdateSandbox Semantics\n\n### Scenario: UpdateSandbox only modifies session value\n\n**GIVEN** an existing session with key `session:{id}`  \n**WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called with new sandbox data  \n**THEN** only the session JSON value is updated using SET with XX flag  \n**AND** expiry and last-activity ZSET entries are NOT modified\n\n### Scenario: UpdateSandbox fails on missing key\n\n**GIVEN** no session key exists for the given session id  \n**WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called  \n**THEN** error is returned indicating key does not exist (Redis: SETXX returns false; Valkey: response not \"OK\")\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID Cleanup\n\n### Scenario: Delete removes session key and both indexes\n\n**GIVEN** an existing session with data in all three keys  \n**WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` is called  \n**THEN** the operation removes:\n- Session key (`session:{id}`) via DEL\n- Member from `session:expiry` ZSET via ZREM\n- Member from `session:last_activity` ZSET via ZREM\n\n### Scenario: Delete executes atomically\n\n**GIVEN** a valid session id  \n**WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` runs  \n**THEN** all delete operations execute in one pipeline/multi block\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: ListExpiredSandboxes Operation\n\n### Scenario: ListExpired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on expiry index\n\n**GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0  \n**WHEN** the implementation queries the index  \n**THEN** it selects members from `session:expiry` with scores from negative infinity to `before.Unix()`  \n**AND** limited to `limit` entries\n\n### Scenario: ListExpired with limit <= 0 returns nil\n\n**GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` called with limit <= 0  \n**WHEN** executed  \n**THEN** returns `nil, nil`\n\n### Scenario: ListExpired loads JSON for each session id\n\n**GIVEN** ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session ids  \n**WHEN** fetching sandbox data  \n**THEN** each id is used to GET the corresponding `session:{id}` key  \n**AND** JSON is unmarshaled to `SandboxInfo`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: ListInactiveSandboxes Operation\n\n### Scenario: ListInactive uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity index\n\n**GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0  \n**WHEN** the implementation queries the index  \n**THEN** it selects members from `session:last_activity` with scores Ōēż `before.Unix()`  \n**AND** limited to `limit` entries\n\n### Scenario: ListInactive with limit <= 0 returns nil\n\n**GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes` called with limit <= 0  \n**WHEN** executed  \n**THEN** returns `nil, nil`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: List Operations Tolerate Missing Keys\n\n### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member is skipped\n\n**GIVEN** a session id returned from ZSET but without corresponding string value  \n**WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs  \n**THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice  \n**AND** the operation does not fail for the whole batch\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n\n### Scenario: Empty session id rejected\n\n**GIVEN** empty session id  \n**WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called  \n**THEN** error is returned\n\n### Scenario: Zero time uses current time\n\n**GIVEN** an existing session  \n**WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with zero time  \n**THEN** `time.Now()` is used as the activity timestamp\n\n### Scenario: Non-zero time uses provided value\n\n**GIVEN** an existing session  \n**WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with non-zero `at` timestamp  \n**THEN** the provided timestamp is used as the activity score in ZADD\n\n### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity requires existing session\n\n**GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key exists  \n**WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called  \n**THEN** error is `ErrNotFound`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Singleton Initialization\n\n### Scenario: Storage returns singleton instance\n\n**GIVEN** `Storage()` is called multiple times  \n**WHEN** after first initialization  \n**THEN** the same store instance is returned every time\n\n### Scenario: Concurrent Storage calls initialize once\n\n**GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()` concurrently  \n**WHEN** they execute concurrently  \n**THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once via `sync.Once`\n\n### Scenario: Init failure triggers fatal log\n\n**GIVEN** store initialization fails  \n**WHEN** `Storage()` is called  \n**THEN** `klog.Fatalf` is called with error message\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Redis and Valkey Equivalence\n\n### Scenario: Both backends implement same interface\n\n**GIVEN** Redis and Valkey stores with equivalent configuration  \n**WHEN** equivalent operations are performed  \n**THEN** both backends produce identical results for:\n- Session CRUD operations\n- Listing expired/inactive sessions\n- Last activity updates\n- Error semantics (`ErrNotFound`)\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Store interface defined in `pkg/store/store.go`\n- [ ] ErrNotFound error defined and returned for missing sessions\n- [ ] Redis implementation in `pkg/store/store_redis.go`\n- [ ] Valkey implementation in `pkg/store/store_valkey.go`\n- [ ] Singleton pattern in `pkg/store/singleton.go` with `Storage()` function\n- [ ] Environment variables parsed correctly for both providers\n- [ ] Password policy enforced (required by default, optional when disabled)\n- [ ] Session key naming uses `session:` prefix\n- [ ] Expiry index maintained via `session:expiry` ZSET\n- [ ] Last activity index maintained via `session:last_activity` ZSET\n- [ ] Atomic operations for Store, Update, 